title: For Sale:  Colt Double Eagle 45ACP NIB 1989
postcontent: We have found an unfired new in the box Colt Double Eagle 45ACP that was made in 1989 with original box and all paperwork. This is a great find and passing it on to someone else that will enjoy this very beautiful Colt. The Colt Double Eagle is a double-action / single action, semi-automatic pistol manufactured by Colt's Manufacturing Company between 1989 and 1997. It was the first double-action semiautomatic pistol offered by the company and was available in standard full-size, as well as in more compact versions. It featured a decocking lever, and was chambered for several calibers. The design of the Double Eagle was based on the Colt M1911 pistol. Magazines are single stack and are identical to magazines shipped with the M1911. This Double Eagle is in mint condition and as if you walked back in 1989 and bought it brand new form the gun shop. It is getting very difficult to find these in NIB condition as most people buy these to fire. This one is ready for either a Colt collector to add to the collection or for the Colt range firing that is ready to take this out and find out what Colt offered in 1989 design and feel. You will be 100% satisfied with this Colt so don’t let it slip by you. Shipping is $25 and free for all military, veterans and law enforcement. Please visit and like our FB page at: DCF FB Page
